. In contrast, in area 7a excitatory responses were most frequent in the Post-S phase (56{\%}). Excitation was particularly infrequent during M (28{\%}) and Pre-S (22{\%}). The incidence of inhibitory responses varied too (4-18{\%}). The time course of inhibition was roughly opposite that of excitation; the highest frequency of inhibitory responses occurred during the saccade.},
