near complete brain. Approximately 200 structures were extracted from the 2-D atlas drawings to create 3-D
annotations. A second version (in 2011) of a refined CCF was constructed to support the scientific objectives
of the Allen Mouse Brain Connectivity Atlas (Oh et al., 2014) where a double-sided and more deeply
annotated framework was needed (Figure 1). During the development, flaws in the 3-D reconstructions were
corrected and the volume was mirrored across the mid-line to create a symmetric space. Eight hundred and
sixty structures were extracted and interpolated to create symmetric 3-D annotations. },
